CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 11, 1958, page 14, reads: "Breaking Ground - This quartet took part in the groundbreaking cermonies last Sunday, for the addition to the Sewickley Community Center, located at 151 Ohio River Blvd., Sewickley. Left to right: Mrs. Ellis Blockson, Anita Thomas, Walter Brannon, president of the board of directors of the center, and Mrs. Edward O'Neil. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Mrs. Ellis Blockson holding shovel, Girl Scout Anita Thomas, Walter Brannon, and Mrs. Edward O'Neil, also holding shovel, gathered for Sewickley Community Center groundbreaking ceremony, 151 Ohio River Boulevard, Sewickley
